{"title_page": "Harold Tennyson, 4th Baron Tennyson", "text_new": "'''Harold Christopher Tennyson, 4th Baron Tennyson''' (25 March 1919{{spaced ndash}}19 October 1991), was a [[United Kingdom|British]] peer. \n\nHe was the oldest son of [[Lionel Tennyson, 3rd Baron Tennyson]] and the [[Clare Tennant|Hon. Clarissa Madeline Georgiana Felicite Tennant]], his first marriage and her second. Harold was the great-grandson of poet [[Alfred Tennyson, 1st Baron Tennyson|Alfred, Lord Tennyson]] and succeeded his father as the '''4th Baron Tennyson''' in 1951.\n\nHe studied at [[Eton College]] and [[Trinity College, Cambridge]] before joining the War Office in 1940. In later life he was co-founder with [[Sir Charles Tennyson]] of the Tennyson Research Centre, Lincoln.\n\nHe died unmarried in 1991, the title passing to his brother Mark. \n\n{{start box}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{succession box|title=[[Baron Tennyson]]|before=[[Lionel Tennyson, 3rd Baron Tennyson|Lionel Tennyson]]|after=[[Mark Tennyson, 5th Baron Tennyson|Mark Tennyson]]|years=}}\n{{end box}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tennyson, Harold Tennyson, 4th Baron}}\n[[Category:1919 births]]\n[[Category:1991 deaths]]\n[[Category:Barons in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{UK-baron-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Harold Christopher Tennyson, 4th Baron Tennyson''' (25 March 1919{{spaced ndash}}19 October 1991), was a [[United Kingdom|British]] peer. \n\nHe was the oldest son of [[Lionel Tennyson, 3rd Baron Tennyson]] and the [[Clare Tennant|Hon. Clarissa Madeline Georgiana Felicite Tennant]], his first marriage and her second. Harold was the great-grandson of poet [[Alfred Tennyson, 1st Baron Tennyson|Alfred, Lord Tennyson]] and succeeded his father as the '''4th Baron Tennyson''' in 1951.\n\nHe studied at [[Eton College]] and [[Trinity College, Cambridge]] before joining the War Office in 1940. In later life he was co-founder with [[Sir Charles Tennyson]] of the Tennyson Research Centre, Lincoln.\n\nHe died unmarried in 1991, the title passing to his brother Mark. \n\n{{start box}}\n{{s-reg|uk}}\n{{succession box|title=[[Baron Tennyson]]|before=[[Lionel Tennyson, 3rd Baron Tennyson|Lional Tennyson]]|after=[[Mark Tennyson, 5th Baron Tennyson|Mark Tennyson]]|years=}}\n{{end box}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tennyson, Harold Tennyson, 4th Baron}}\n[[Category:1919 births]]\n[[Category:1991 deaths]]\n[[Category:Barons in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{UK-baron-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Valetude", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harold_Tennyson,_4th_Baron_Tennyson"}
{"title_page": "Slatinky", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Slatinky\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=Slatinky.jpg|image_shield=Slatinky_CoA_CZ.png|image_flag=\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[Olomouc Region|Olomouc]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Prost\u011bjov District|Prost\u011bjov]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|49|32|53|N|17|5|13|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=8.02\n|population_total=492|population_as_of=2006\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=272\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=783&nbsp;42\n|website=http://slatinky.cz\n}}\n\n'''Slatinky''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Prost\u011bjov District]] in the [[Olomouc Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|8.02|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 492 (as at 28&nbsp;August 2006).\n\nSlatinky lies approximately {{convert|9|km|mi|0}} north of [[Prost\u011bjov]], {{convert|13|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-west of [[Olomouc]], and {{convert|201|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} east of [[Prague]].\n\nThere is a natural monument [[V\u00e1penice (natural monument)|V\u00e1penice]] in the southern part of the territory of the municipality.<ref name=\"AOPK\"/>\n\n==Notes==\n<references>\n<ref name=\"AOPK\">{{cite web\n | title = PP V\u00e1penice\n | work = \u00dast\u0159edn\u00ed seznam ochrany p\u0159\u00edrody\n | publisher = Nature Conservation Agency of the Czech Republic (AOPK \u010cR)\n | url = http://drusop.nature.cz/ost/chrobjekty/zchru/index.php?frame&SHOW_ONE=1&ID=1243\n | accessdate = 2014-05-02\n | archiveurl = \n | archivedate = }}</ref>\n</references>\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Slatinky}}\n*[http://www.olomouc.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0713/ Olomouc Regional Statistical Office: Municipalities of Prost\u011b